cacert_file.description: A file containing the ca certificate to use in case ssl certificate is not from a standard chain

insecure.description: Disable SSL verification of API calls

password.description: Password in case of using basic auth

token.description: The application token used to connect to Gitea.

username.description: Username in case of using basic auth

organization.description: The organization that owns the forked repo

owner.description: The owner or owning organization of the repository to fork

repo.description: The name of the repository to fork

block.description:
`gitea_fork` manages repository fork to the current user or an organisation
Forking a repository to a dedicated user is currently unsupported
Creating a fork using this resource without an organisation will create the fork in the executors name

name.description: Name of the git hook to configure

repo.description: The repository that this hook belongs too.

user.description: The user (or organisation) owning the repo this hook belongs too

block.description:
`gitea_git_hook` manages git hooks on a repository.
import is currently not supported

WARNING: using this resource requires to enable server side hookswhich are known to cause [security issues](https://github.com/go-gitea/gitea/pull/13058)!

if you want to procede, you need to enable server side hooks as stated [here](https://docs.gitea.io/en-us/config-cheat-sheet/#security-security)

key_id.description: The ID of the GPG key

block.description: `gitea_gpg_key` manages gpg keys that are associated with the current user.

confidential_client.description: If set to false, it will be a public client (PKCE will be required)

full_name.description: The display name of the organisation. Defaults to the value of `name`.

name.description: The name of the organisation without spaces.

repos.description: List of all Repositories that are part of this organisation

visibility.description: Flag is this organisation should be publicly visible or not.

website.description: A link to a website with more information about this organisation.

block.description:
`gitea_org` manages a gitea organisation.

Organisations are a way to group repositories and abstract permission management in a gitea instance.

key.description: An armored SSH key to add

read_only.description: Describe if the key has only read access or read/write

title.description: Title of the key to add

username.description: User to associate with the added key

block.description: `gitea_public_key` manages ssh key that are associated with users.

archive_on_destroy.description: Set to 'true' to archive the repository instead of deleting on destroy.

auto_init.description: Flag if the repository should be initiated with the configured values

default_branch.description: The default branch of the repository. Defaults to `main`

gitignores.description:
A specific gitignore that should be commited to the repositoryon creation if `auto_init` is set to `true`
Need to exist in the gitea instance

has_issues.description: A flag if the repository should have issue management enabled or not.

has_projects.description: A flag if the repository should have the native project management enabled or not.

has_pull_requests.description: A flag if the repository should acceppt pull requests or not.

has_wiki.description: A flag if the repository should have the native wiki enabled or not.

issue_labels.description:
The Issue Label configuration to be used in this repository.
Need to exist in the gitea instance

license.description:
The license under which the source code of this repository should be.
Need to exist in the gitea instance

migration_mirror_interval.description: valid time units are 'h', 'm', 's'. 0 to disable automatic sync

private.description: Flag if the repository should be private or not.

website.description: A link to a website with more information.

block.description:
`gitea_repository` manages a gitea repository.

Per default this repository will be initializiled with the provided configuration (gitignore, License etc.).
If the `username` property is set to a organisation name, the provider will try to look if this organisation exists and create the repository under the organisation scope.

Repository migrations have some properties that are not available to regular repositories. These are all prefixed with `migration_`.

approval_whitelist_teams.description:
Only reviews from allowlisted teams will count to the required
								approvals. Without approval allowlist, reviews from anyone with
								write access count to the required approvals.

approval_whitelist_users.description:
Only reviews from allowlisted users will count to the required
								approvals. Without approval allowlist, reviews from anyone with
								write access count to the required approvals.

block_merge_on_official_review_requests.description:
Merging will not be possible when it has official
								review requests, even if there are enough approvals.

block_merge_on_outdated_branch.description: Merging will not be possible when head branch is behind base branch.

block_merge_on_rejected_reviews.description:
Merging will not be possible when changes are
								requested by official reviewers, even if there are enough
								approvals.

dismiss_stale_approvals.description:
When new commits that change the content of the pull request
								are pushed to the branch, old approvals will be dismissed.

enable_approval_whitelist.description: True if a approval whitelist is used.

enable_merge_whitelist.description: True if a merge whitelist is used.

enable_push.description:
Anyone with write access will be allowed to push to this branch
								(but not force push), add a whitelist users or teams to limit
								access.

enable_push_whitelist.description: True if a push whitelist is used.

enable_status_check.description:
Require status checks to pass before merging. When enabled,
								commits must first be pushed to another branch, then merged
								or pushed directly to a branch that matches this rule after
								status checks have passed. If no contexts are matched, the
								last commit must be successful regardless of context

merge_whitelist_teams.description: Allow only allowlisted teams to merge pull requests into this branch.

merge_whitelist_users.description: Allow only allowlisted users to merge pull requests into this branch.

push_whitelist_deploy_keys.description: Allow deploy keys with write access to push. Requires enable_push to be set to true.

push_whitelist_teams.description: Allowlisted teams for pushing. Requires enable_push to be set to true.

push_whitelist_users.description: Allowlisted users for pushing. Requires enable_push to be set to true.

require_signed_commits.description: Reject pushes to this branch if they are unsigned or unverifiable.

required_approvals.description: Allow only to merge pull request with enough positive reviews.

status_check_patterns.description:
Enter patterns to specify which status checks must pass before
								branches can be merged into a branch that matches this rule.
								Each line specifies a pattern. Patterns cannot be empty.

block.description: This resource allows you to create and manage branch protections for repositories.

read_only.description: Whether this key has read or read/write access

repository.description: The ID of the repository where the deploy key belongs to

block.description:
`gitea_repository_key` manages a deploy key for a single gitea_repository.

Every key needs a unique name and unique key, i.e. no key can be added twice to the same repo

branch_filter.description: Set branch filter on the webhook, e.g. `"*"`

content_type.description: The content type of the payload. It can be `json`, or `form`

events.description: A list of events that will trigger the webhool, e.g. `["push"]`

block.description: This resource allows you to create and manage webhooks for repositories.

can_create_repos.description: Flag if the Teams members should be able to create Rpositories in the Organisation

include_all_repositories.description: Flag if the Teams members should have access to all Repositories in the Organisation

organisation.description: The organisation which this Team is part of.

permission.description:
Permissions associated with this Team
Can be `none`, `read`, `write`, `admin` or `owner`

repositories.description: List of Repositories that should be part of this team

units.description:
List of types of Repositories that should be allowed to be created from Team members.
Can be `repo.code`, `repo.issues`, `repo.ext_issues`, `repo.wiki`, `repo.pulls`, `repo.releases`, `repo.projects` and/or `repo.ext_wiki`

block.description: `gitea_team` manages Team that are part of an organisation.

members.description: The user names of the members of the team.

block.description: `gitea_team_members` manages all members of a single team. This resource will be recreated on member changes.

username.description: The username of the team member.

block.description: `gitea_team_membership` manages a single user's membership of a single team.

name.description: The name of the Access Token

scopes.description: List of string representations of scopes for the token

block.description:
`gitea_token` manages gitea Access Tokens.

Due to upstream limitations (see https://gitea.com/gitea/go-sdk/issues/610) this resource
can only be used with username/password provider configuration.

WARNING:
Tokens will be stored in the terraform state!

active.description: Flag if this user should be active or not

admin.description: Flag if this user should be an administrator or not

force_password_change.description: Flag if the user defined password should be overwritten or not

login_name.description: The login name can differ from the username

must_change_password.description: Flag if the user should change the password after first login

password.description: Password to be set for the user

prohibit_login.description: Flag if the user should not be allowed to log in (bot user)

send_notification.description: Flag to send a notification about the user creation to the defined `email`

username.description: Username of the user to be created

visibility.description: Visibility of the user. Can be `public`, `limited` or `private`

block.description:
`gitea_user` manages a native gitea user.

If you are using OIDC or other kinds of authentication mechanisms you can still try to managessh keys or other ressources this way
